  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="comment-body markdown-body markdown-format js-comment-body">
          <p><em>From <a href="https://code.google.com/u/113327232123772191739/">LudwigBr...@gmail.com</a> on March 06, 2011 02:09:34</em></p>

<p>Just had a chance to look at this now. The code is fine and it is probably not essential to have a max zoom level in the code.<br>
However, is it possible to set the max zoom level for offline rendering somewhere when creating the map file? I personally find that beyond zoom level 18 the map does not improve any more and certain irregularities of OSM maps really begin to show (e.g. lines not straight or parallel, angles of rectangular buildings usually not at 90deg etc.), so I like to suppress the user's ability to zoom in further.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

